chiropractic here in Medford, Long Island. And one of the big things is to make
sure you use your knees, but the second most important thing is not to twist.
So the proper way to shovel, bend the knees, shovel, but instead of twisting,
to throw the snow, you should turn and drop it. If you have a large pile of snow

knees, lift, do not twist, put the turn, and dump the snow. Bend the knees, lift
with the knees, do not twist, turn your body, and throw the snow. If it's very
heavy, do not even throw the snow. Turn, walk, and dump the snow. Believe me,
